Dylan’s father committed suicide when he was only a teenager, leaving behind no will and no plan for his things. At the age of 16, Dylan had to grow up quickly as he catalogued his father’s things and decided what to do with his assets. When he met Randi, they fell in love quickly and discovered many coincidences on their life paths. Their Dad’s birthdays were only 1 day apart and died at the same age. Together they have helped one another heal through their losses and they come to this reading with Fleur together hoping to help one another release the last remnants of grief.
Join the Moving Beyond Community at Patreon to see pictures of Dylan and his Dad together. www.patreon.com/movingbeyond

*Save this post to serve as a reminder for when you’re pushing to think your way into intuition*

2022.

My word for the year was “germinate” (to begin to grow after a period of dormancy) and it held true. Many times this year I’ve said the words “I think we’ll look back at this year as the year we planted seeds & hustled”. & we did! I’m a little early with my year at a glance review, but here it is- most of all, there are so many people to thank. 

It truly was a startup vibe in all ways. I think it hasn’t (yet) been evident from the outside -but, on the inside, we completely changed. In 2021, the team was mostly me and one assistant. In 2022 we brought on over 20 people in various roles; 8 of them ran with us as a part of the inner team for most of the year. We even had a paid intern over the summer! Everyone pitched in. It was all hands on deck and every hand that was there was, and is, there for the right heart-centered reasons. I hope if you’ve connected with a member of the team in the last year, you feel the heart. It’s been my biggest gratitude this year, to watch in awe at the team of people that’s assembled and how they show up. 

Everything we put out this year, I’m proud of. We (created) and ran 6, month-long, mentorship courses, 2 retreats, 20 free masterclasses, and had published interviews in 24 major global publications. I continued doing 3 readings almost every day, 7 live shows between LA, NYC, and London and we launched a new podcast season & worked or went to 14 cities in 7 countries. I have no idea the number of students but I believe it’s way over 3000. I can’t thank each and every single one of you enough. 
It was also a year that required tremendous inner work to keep up. Not everything succeeded and navigating this new kind of business was a learning process in itself. I had a moment of - wait, who is the CEO that’s listed?! 😂 am I a CEO? -Which also meant I had a lot of growing to do. Most of all in trust & surrender, and learning that most problems will ultimately solve themselves but also knowing how to spot the ones that won’t. It is was the first year I’ve fully felt I know who I am. I came to know my values and boundaries, I re-committed to my own deeper connection to self and spirit.

Sending you off into 2023 with one question- how will you prioritize self trust & intuition this year? 

Why this question? In order to create you must trust yourself. In order to trust yourself you must have a deep connection with your internal feedback (intuition). 

Without these two important internal sources of wisdom, how will you know what’s right for you this year, where to focus your energy and how to create your dreams? One of my biggest lessons as a teacher this year was that intuition and self trust require each other to thrive. You cannot have self trust without a strong intuition, and you cannot follow your intuition without a deep trust in yourself. You can of course cultivate both, and it will change your life. If you’d like to start the year of with a bang, see my link in bio for resources, classes and more to start 2023 empowered.

Wishing you and yours a wonderful start to a new year ❤️

When Luisa was 19 she found out her Dad had a daughter, her younger sister, Pietra. While she was living in Brazil, Luisa got to know Pietra, showering her with love and everything a big sister wants to do for their younger sibling. Life took Luisa to the U.S. for 8 years and gradually they lost touch. During the pandemic, Pietra felt more and more isolated, battling depression and one day, she took her own life. Devastated, Luisa has tried to understand what happened and has wondered if there was anything she could have done to help save Pietra.

I’ve been writing a lot in the last few weeks- new ideas on intuition & then putting them into practice. I keep coming back to a topic I heard @gabormatemd speak on, that we speak about anxiety (adhd, etc) as if we inherit it but what inherit is actually a sensitive nervous system. It truly plays into my work as a teacher, because I believe that sensitivity is both the gift and seemingly the curse (when overwhelmed). It’s the gift when it births intuition, an ability to tune into what isn’t so readily witnessed with the other senses. It’s the curse when we live in a fried state of everything is too much, or go the opposite direction and feel nothing. 

The sensitivity is yours, and with the right tools it can be channeled into intuition instead of overwhelm. It’s with all these ideas that I start planning my February mentorship course, can’t wait to see some of you there.

Losing a loved one to suicide is a blow that most of us can’t fathom how we could move beyond that experience. Kate is now the author of a book, “The Full Spirit Workout” that empowers to break through the those less tangible roadblocks to achieving your goals — mental and emotional baggage, deep seated insecurity, self judgement and overwhelming stress and anxiety. In an emotional session with Fleur, Kate is given the gift of knowing she’s on the right track and a few other very special messages.

For Mary, sending her second child, Owen, to college was an exciting time. She never imagined that one Sunday evening he would vanish without a trace. Growing up, Owen was a good kid, responsible, caring and rarely got into any trouble. He spent his time writing songs with friends, exploring the outdoors and making his family laugh. He’d only been at college for a few short weeks when Owen’s roommate called his parents and said that he was missing. They immediately launched a search and spent weeks searching for Owen. They’ve never found his backpack and are uncertain what happened to the money he took out of an ATM. Three weeks after Owen went missing, they recovered his body in the Willamette River. When the report from the Medical Examiner led to more questions than answers, Mary and her family felt even more lost and confused. Struggling to move beyond the grief of losing Owen, while trying to understand what happened, Mary hopes that Fleur will connect with Owen and help bring a little closure to their loss.

Happy Women’s Day 

Woman- identifying persons make up 89% of my demographic on this platform and 95% of my offerings. I love you all. I am eternally a feminist, a deep believer in the innate feminine wisdom, the intuitive knowledge that so deeply resonates within every single one of us but most often gets noticed first in the feminine expression of life. 
There are times when I resisted my femininity. I thought it was better, stronger, more powerful to do business in a masculine way.

But now, not at all. I’ve got an all female team, after every weekly meeting we take some time for sharing and gratitude, once a month I pull an oracle card for each member on the team, we are all about teamwork, we collaborate, everyone has a voice and I’m amazed- never before has it felt so powerful. It’s such a joy to get to rewrite my own beliefs around what it means to be a woman, what it means to run a business as a woman, and why there is no weakness in prioritizing a flow rather than a force. It’s a lifelong reprogramming and I’m here for it ♥️

Fun fact, I was told roughly 7 years ago (after a focus group study) that I wasn’t good for their media angle, because “I alienated a male audience” 😅 I’m ok with it & even better, I think tides are changing 💋

It’s the night before my 33rd birthday 🥳 and life gave me some reflection time. Delayed flights and reroutes have me looking back while traveling (travel is surely 100% the years theme and, the best time for reflection!) - & all that time has me landing on gratitude, especially that I get to teach. Leading retreats was my absolute favorite thing of the past year. For many reasons: seeing firsthand that literally everyone (no matter what you’ve been through) can and will find their way back to themselves, the delight of watching big hearted, curious people become best friends, and the joy of getting to facilitate some energetic shifts that make people feel things they didn’t think they could. What a miracle. To get to see people’s realness is a rarity in a world that moves so fast, and lucky lucky me that I get to see it daily. I don’t take it for granted and it is such an honor to get to guide you back to you- however our paths crossed, in big ways or small.

If you’re ready for a little more, join me in Italy for the august retreat. Especially if you haven’t found YOU yet, because I got you! Do you find yourself trapped in the suffocating grip of feeling stuck? 

Perhaps you are yearning for something more, something different, but you are unsure of how to break free?

If you’re reading this, I know you’re not new to self exploration- you’ve already tried some combination of meditating, positive affirmations, and journaling in an effort tofind yourself. It's not your fault that it isn't working and you still feel stuck.

The Intuition Activation Retreat works because it goes a step further, to access your intuition: 

1. Your nervous system needs a reboot. When you’ve been through a time of turmoil, your body cannot remember how peace feels. Intuition cannot exist in a stressed-out system. This retreat employs cutting-edge techniques geared towards rewiring your neural brain pathways using a body-based therapeutic approach that will dissolve stress, grief, anxiety and fear. Past participants have told me it was the first time they have truly felt peace. 
2. You cannot over give. When your empathic overwhelm is louder than your inner voice, your intuition cannot exist. During this retreat, you will learn to separate your energy from others. Creating energetic boundaries will reclaim your sense of self-trust, and give you an accurate ability to energetically read others as well as yourself. 
3. You need to feel connected. Whether you call it Spirit, the Divine, Love, God or Goddess-when was the last time you knew it in your bones? My favorite testimonial came from a participant at our last retreat: “Thank you for helping me feel the universe within myself”. 

One of the key reasons this kind of deep profound work can happen at retreat however is I bring energy workers along with me. In the last retreat, 6 staff worked alongside me each morning, each carefully vetted and trained in energy medicine. When you’re going through profound inner transformation, we’re right there allowing that movement to happen and creating a safe container in which to let it release. More room created to hear yourself clearly

Have you ever witnessed one person cross your boundaries repeatedly and turn around to honor someone else’s? It can be maddening when you have said, explained, begged someone to change. We’re all in energetic conversation, all the time. 

Boundaries fascinate me. And, they’re always a mirror. If your interpersonal boundaries suck, I guarantee your energetic boundaries suck too. & vice versa. 

Out-tuition is that exchange between people - and your boundaries speak energetically. Of course you want to speak up, but if your energetic boundaries are strong: you won’t need to scream it.
The added benefit- you preserve your energy and don’t walk around drained. 
The boundaries module in The Intuition Mastery Method is aimed to help you with your boundaries- to claim your space and own your energy. When you’re not carrying everyone else’s stuff, your space is free to fill with useful intuition

my main girl 

She’s getting older. 11. Whenever people ask they think I mean 11 months, which is really cute. She has a lively spirit that could fool anyone. But, her body is growing a bit older and little health things aren’t so little anymore! It’s been a profound learning experience to navigate intuition when your worst fears get triggered. I want my intuition working in order to take care of her, and yet the anxiety that hits when she’s unwell is super real. I use my own Intuition Mastery Method in these times to identify where my intuitive flow is getting a bit stuck, and in these months it’s been NERVOUS SYSTEM for me. 
Many of my students look at anxiety as a x vs y. Is it anxiety or is it intuition? But I see anxiety as simply being a louder response in the body covering up the intuition. It’s not one or the other- anxiety is just the louder voice. Making sure I do my 1 minute regulation practices a few times a day, gives my nervous system the space to receive what I need to- and neutralizes the anxiety. It’s a simple practice, but massively helpful. Together we’ve navigated a few health scares, and since she can’t talk I’m grateful I’m tuned in to help her 💚
Intuition Mastery Method is for everyone 🦋

dancing, getting in the body, letting yourself feel and, land= embodiment.
It’s an important part of the Intuition wheel part found in The Brain & The Emotions module. 
It is KEY to a high functioning intuition. It’s key to amping up your intuition. It’s so important that I bring an embodiment coach to every retreat. 
What does the body have to do with the brain? We have more neurons that go body —> brain than we do the other way around. It’s actually 80% body to brain. That’s wild. And, very helpful. We’ve been taught to try and relax into intuitive states from the brain, and that really isn’t how it works best. 

Embodiment was one of my personal biggest blocks in the intuition wheel when I first started this work, and the greatest area of growth. Go move your body, on your own or with some loved ones 😘
